						<div class="postbody">I'm not new to programming, but I'm new to assembly and low-level programming concepts and so far I'm having an easy time grasping the concepts and everything, but there's one thing right now that I'm having trouble with.  Can you write and hold multiple pieces of data (such as multiple sprites) in a single address, like $2007, or can it only hold a single piece of datum (such as a single sprite) at a time?  If you can write multiple pieces of data, what's the limit that it can hold?</div>

